President Obama has nominated Steven O'Donnell to serve as the United States Marshal for the District of Rhode Island. O'Donnell has a distinguished career in law enforcement, including 22 years with the Rhode Island State Police Department. He currently teaches courses on organized crime, criminal justice, and undercover operations at Roger Williams University and Salve Regina University. O'Donnell is a graduate of the FBI National Academy and holds a BS from the University of New Haven and an MS from Salve Regina University. President Obama commended O'Donnell's commitment and courage in serving his country and expressed his confidence in his ability to continue protecting the American people as a U.S. Marshal.